description:
Very nice little Thai spot near Japantown! We were in the mood for some Thai cuisine and Sweet Lime was a perfect fit for our party of 5. We tried the papaya salad, fresh rolls, and vegan crispy rolls for appetizers - very flavorful & would order again. 

The entrees were equally tasty & fresh - zuki noodles, pad thai, yellow veggie curry, and green curry with duck. {*I don't eat duck but my dinner guests loved it... :) }

The bananas foster with ginger sorbet and mango with sticky rice were an excellent way to cap off our little feast. Service was very friendly & attentive - thanks to fellow Yelpers for leading us to this place!
